are_module_finite_HModule_of_HModule_prime_X4_curve}) — the algebraic counterpart of iter-036, transporting finiteness rather than finrank across the corner-bridge, via Mathlib's $\Module.\mathtt{Finite.equiv}$. Iter-038 → iter-046 build the H⁰ Module.Finite ladder (curve specialisations + carrier predicates + Stein input + global-sections evaluation iso + producer chain end-to-end for $\IsHModuleHomFinite\,k\,C\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)$); iter-047 lays foundational parameterised Čech infrastructure; iter-048 appends the Čech-side acyclicity carrier predicate and abstract consumer; iter-049 appends the top-supremum HModule transport (Theorems~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_of_isCechAcyclicCover_top} and~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_of_isCechAcyclicCover_top_curve}) — the universe $u \to u+1$ bridge that lets iter-053+ ultimately consume iter-048's $\Subsingleton$ on $\HModulePrime$ at the lattice supremum to derive the genus carrier $\Module.\mathtt{Finite}\,k\,(\HModule\,k\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)\,1)$ at universe $u+1$; iter-050 packages the Čech-vs-derived comparison iso as a $\Prop$-valued typeclass $\Scheme.\HasCechToHModuleIso$ with $\Classical.\mathtt{choice}$-based extractor (Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_cechToHModuleIso}) and instance-driven \emph{top-supremum} consumers (Theorems~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_of_hasCechToHModuleIso_top} and~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_of_hasCechToHModuleIso_top_curve}); iter-051 (this iteration) appends the symmetric instance-driven \emph{intermediate-supremum} consumers (Theorems~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_prime_supr_of_hasCechToHModuleIso} and~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_prime_supr_of_hasCechToHModuleIso_curve}) — landing $\Subsingleton\,(\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,(\bigsqcup\mathcal U))$ at universe $u$, the exact form iter-053+ needs to instantiate $\IsAffineHModuleVanishing\,k\,C\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)$ for an affine open via a basic-open cover. The remaining work — Step 4 (the sub